<use f='linux-4.18.y/drivers/tty/tty_ldisc.c' l='739' u='c' c='tty_ldisc_hangup'/>
<doc f='linux-4.18.y/drivers/tty/tty_ldisc.c' l='646'>/**
 *	tty_ldisc_reinit	-	reinitialise the tty ldisc
 *	@tty: tty to reinit
 *	@disc: line discipline to reinitialize
 *
 *	Completely reinitialize the line discipline state, by closing the
 *	current instance, if there is one, and opening a new instance. If
 *	an error occurs opening the new non-N_TTY instance, the instance
 *	is dropped and tty-&gt;ldisc reset to NULL. The caller can then retry
 *	with N_TTY instead.
 *
 *	Returns 0 if successful, otherwise error code &lt; 0
 */</doc>
